------------------------------------------------------------
SECTION 1 — SYSTEM OVERVIEW
------------------------------------------------------------

Goal:
Build a wearable test platform with:
- Distributed battery power
- 1-joint assist (knee)
- Motion energy recovery
- Microfluidic cooling loop
- Central compute (Jetson)
- Real-time control (FPGA or MCU for V1)

NO flight. NO full-body actuation.

------------------------------------------------------------
SECTION 2 — BILL OF MATERIALS (V1)
------------------------------------------------------------

COMPUTE
- NVIDIA Jetson Orin Nano Developer Kit
- 128GB NVMe SSD
- 5V/4A regulated supply (for Jetson)

CONTROL
- STM32 Nucleo board (V1 instead of FPGA for simplicity)
- CAN or UART interface module

POWER
- 6x Li-ion battery packs (3.7V nominal, flat pouch style)
- BMS (Battery Management System, 6S or modular parallel setup)
- DC-DC converters:
  - 24V rail (actuators)
  - 12V rail (pump, peripherals)
  - 5V rail (logic)

ACTUATION (1 LEG)
- 1x Brushless DC motor (500–1000W peak)
- Motor driver (FOC capable, e.g., VESC)
- Harmonic drive or high-ratio gearbox (≥ 50:1)
- Knee joint bracket (custom or machined)

ENERGY HARVESTING
- Backdrive-enabled motor (same actuator used regen)
- Bridge rectifier / regen-compatible controller

MICROFLUIDIC SYSTEM
- Micro pump (12V, 0.5–1.5 L/min)
- 2–3 mm ID silicone tubing
- Small reservoir (100–250 mL)
- Compact heat exchanger (radiator plate)
- Dielectric coolant or water-glycol mix

STRUCTURE
- Kevlar/UHMWPE fabric (spider-silk analog)
- Aluminum frame pieces (6061-T6)
- Fasteners (M3/M4 stainless)

SENSORS
- IMU (MPU-6050 or BNO055)
- Temperature sensors (DS18B20 or thermistors)
- Current sensors (INA219 or similar)
- Optional: flex sensors for joints

SAFETY
- Inline fuses (each battery segment)
- Emergency cutoff switch
- Thermal cutoff (battery + motor)

------------------------------------------------------------
SECTION 3 — POWER ARCHITECTURE
------------------------------------------------------------

BATTERY CONFIG:
- Parallel packs for capacity OR
- Series (6S) for higher voltage (recommended for motors)

MAIN BUS:
- Battery → BMS → Main Fuse → Power Distribution

RAILS:
- 24V → Motor driver
- 12V → Pump + cooling
- 5V → Jetson + logic

