------------------------------------------------------------
SECTION 6 — MECHANICAL ASSEMBLY
------------------------------------------------------------

STEP 1 — FRAME
- Build knee brace frame (thigh + shin segments)
- Mount hinge aligned with natural knee axis

STEP 2 — MOTOR INSTALL
- Attach motor to thigh section
- Connect gearbox → knee joint

STEP 3 — BATTERY PLACEMENT
- Distribute packs:
  - 2x chest
  - 2x back
  - 2x thighs

STEP 4 — BACK MODULE
- Mount:
  - Jetson
  - Pump
  - Reservoir
  - Radiator plate

STEP 5 — FLUID LINES
- Route tubing along suit interior
- Secure with clips (no movement)

STEP 6 — WIRING
- Route power lines along frame
- Keep signal wires separate from power

STEP 7 — SENSOR MOUNTING
- IMU on torso centerline
- Temp sensors on:
  - Batteries
  - Motor
  - Jetson

------------------------------------------------------------
SECTION 7 — SOFTWARE LOGIC (BASIC)
------------------------------------------------------------

JETSON:
- Reads IMU + user motion
- Sends desired torque commands

STM32:
- Reads sensors in real time
- Controls motor driver
- Enforces limits

CONTROL LOOP:

IF knee flex detected:
    assist motion (apply torque)

IF braking phase:
    enable regen → charge battery

IF temperature > threshold:
    increase pump speed

IF fault:
    cut motor + alert

------------------------------------------------------------
SECTION 8 — TESTING SEQUENCE
------------------------------------------------------------

TEST 1: POWER ONLY
- Verify voltage rails
- No load

TEST 2: CONTROL
- Sensor readings stable
- IMU calibrated

TEST 3: MOTOR (OFF BODY)
- Spin motor unloaded
- Test regen braking

TEST 4: COOLING LOOP
- Run pump
- Check for leaks

TEST 5: PARTIAL WEAR
- Attach to leg only
- Low torque assist

TEST 6: FULL SYSTEM
- Gradual load increase
- Monitor temps + current

------------------------------------------------------------
SECTION 9 — DO NOT DO (CRITICAL)
------------------------------------------------------------

- Do NOT mount flywheel in V1
- Do NOT exceed motor current limits
- Do NOT run without BMS
- Do NOT ignore heat buildup
- Do NOT test at full power immediately

